pkgc:ID_158205694 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2020-05-01"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel "You will work with Games team members -- product managers, game designers, product designers, engineers, QA, marketers, editors, customer support, and data analysts -- to transform our current technology stack into something that is scalable, performant, and serves Games’ long-term product strategy and goals. This includes developing a roadmap to support a growing user base on both web and mobile apps. As an essential member of the Games Product Team reporting to the Product Director, you will help drive to Game’s long-term product strategy and priorities." ;
    pkg:sourceMap "careerDevelopment.mm" .

pkgc:ID_1583133586 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2025-09-19"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel "prioritized features based on impact, available data, feasibility - level of effort, number of unknowns" ;
    pkg:sourceMap "careerDevelopment.mm" .

pkgc:ID_1583569658 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2020-05-01"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel "The Physical Store team is looking for a Product Manager of Catalog and Assortment based in Seattle or New York. As a Product Manager, you will be responsible for working with other consumables-focused businesses and product owners across the organization to develop and utilize mechanisms to support data quality and defect reduction, create and enforce requirements and timelines, and execute new initiatives. Your direct responsibility will be to manage slices of the catalog to deliver best-in-class customer experiences. You will deliver high confidence data accuracy for store assortment across product lifespan from new item to discontinuance and become a catalog expert in physical grocery. You will coordinate across multiple retail teams (e.g., catalog, buying/vendor management, product/program management, operations), build scalable processes, and support your teammates. S/he will be able to grow their abilities to extend to new concepts of selection curation for physical stores over tim" ;
    pkg:sourceMap "careerDevelopment.mm" .

